# Senior Smart Contract Engineer \- MAX LRT \+ Strategy Developer Task

**Description**

We are looking for a Senior Smart Contract Engineer, with expertise in DeFi, Solidity, Foundry, and in TypeScript to complete a task as part of our interview process. The task involves creating a simple strategy for a MAX LRT Vault.

The task is to create a looping strategy on AAVE V3 that can be used as a tokenized strategy by the Yieldnest Max LRT Vault.

You may choose whatever asset pair you prefer for the looping but they should be ETH and ETH derivatives. (For example: wstETH/ETH, cbETH/ETH) to mitigate the liquidation risk.

Additionally, a function that provides a rate of the value of the tokenized strategy asset in ETH should be included. Example: 1 token of ynLoopWstETHa is worth 1.3 ETH. This is required for the YieldNest Max vault to evaluate the value of its holdings in this particular asset.

You may inherit [https://github.com/yieldnest/yieldnest-vault/blob/eth-max-vault/src/BaseVault.sol](https://github.com/yieldnest/yieldnest-vault/blob/eth-max-vault/src/BaseVault.sol)  
If you believe it’s a good fit for your implementation. If not,, feel free to use, another Base strategy, such as [https://github.com/yearn/tokenized-strategy](https://github.com/yearn/tokenized-strategy) if you believe it’s a better fit. The language must be Solidity.

Write a README.md file that briefly describes the architecture decisions and made and states the security assumptions made by the implementation. 

Write a few tests that showcase how the strategy works if deployed on mainnet (simulate any deposits/allocations necessary for the Aave market to allow a successful deposit and loop execution). Write all tests using foundry. Full coverage not required, but enough to demonstrate the happy path works and to give you confidence the implementation is correct and secure.

## 

## Base structure \- ynXYZx \- YieldNest (Asset XYZ) MAX LRT

The YieldNest DAO will have the flexibility to add or remove strategies and MAX LRTs over time. Each MAX LRT will eventually evolve into its own “SubDAO,” maintaining its unique governance and strategy. The objective is to keep the number of MAX LRTs as minimal and focused as possible while ensuring maximum efficiency and low-risk, high-utility strategies.

### Base Configuration for MAX LRT Deployment

![][image3]

The minimal requirements for deploying each MAX LRT are:

* **Set Key Parameters**:  
  * Price asset: **ETH**  
  * Primary underlying asset: **wETH**  
  * Accounting layer: **ETH L1**  
  * underlying assets:  
    1. wETH

### YieldNest LRT Strategies

The YieldNest MAX LRTs (ynXYZx) have been designed with composable strategies in mind. The ynETHx can be seen as a glue that will account for and track all its underlying strategies and combine them into one liquid token. This is easier to manage and will separate and remove complexity from the ynETHx to the LRT strategies.
